//sqflite:
//SQFlite is a Flutter plugin for using a local database.
//It allows you to CRUD data in a local SQLite database.
//SQFlite is a lightweight way to store data locally, and it is suitable for storing large amounts of data.
//SQFlite is a simple way to save and retrieve data, but it is not suitable for storing sensitive data like passwords or API keys.

QLite plugin for Flutter. Supports iOS, Android and MacOS.
    Support transactions and batches
    Automatic version managment during open
    Helpers for insert/query/update/delete queries
    DB operation executed in a background thread on iOS and Android
Other platforms support:
    Linux/Windows/DartVM support using sqflite_common_ffi
    Experimental Web support using sqflite_common_ffi_web.